  ],
  "text": "Firefox's Servo-based CSS style system integrates Gecko (Mozilla's layout engine) with Servo (the Rust-based CSS engine) through a well-structured pipeline in the layout/style/ directory.\n\n1. **ServoStyleSet** (layout/style/ServoStyleSet.h, layout/style/ServoStyleSet.cpp): The primary entry point for style resolution. This class manages the set of style sheets that apply to a document, backed by a Servo Stylist. Key methods include StyleDocument() which performs a Servo traversal to compute style for all dirty nodes in the document, and ResolveStyleLazily() which resolves style for elements without assuming the style has been resolved.\n\n2. **ServoBindings** (layout/style/ServoBindings.h): Provides FFI (Foreign Function Interface) declarations for Gecko-to-Servo communication. It defines Servo_* C functions like Servo_StyleSet_RuleChanged, Servo_CssRules_GetStyleRuleAt, and many other FFI functions that allow C++ code to call Servo's Rust implementation. These bindings are generated via cbindgen.\n\n3. **RestyleManager** (layout/style/RestyleManager.h, layout/style/RestyleManager.cpp): Manages the scheduling and execution of style recalculations. It coordinates with ServoStyleSet to handle DOM changes and determine which elements need restyling. It maintains restyle generation counters and tracks which frames have been invalidated.\n\n4. **ServoUtils** (layout/style/ServoUtils.h): Provides utility functions for Servo traversal state management, including IsInServoTraversal() which checks if the current thread is executing within a Servo style traversal, and utility functions like InitializeServo() and ShutdownServo() for lifecycle management.\n\n5. **moz.build** (layout/style/moz.build): The Mozilla build configuration file that lists all source files in layout/style/. It includes 276 C++ source files and numerous header files organized by category (animations, rules, parsing, etc.), showing the comprehensive scope of the style system.\n\nThe integration flow: RestyleManager detects style invalidation → schedules restyling through ServoStyleSet → ServoStyleSet invokes Servo's traversal via ServoBindings FFI calls → ServoUtils provides utilities to check traversal state → computed styles are returned to Gecko for layout and rendering."
}

